Stellenbosch FC have announced the promotion of youngster Jayden Adams, who has penned a long-term contract. Adams have been playing in the Multichoice Diski Challenge from the beginning of the season. The teenager managed five goals and four assists in 22 starts in the MDC this season,. His promotion will come as a huge boost for coach Steve Barker as they preparing for the Absa Premiership resumption. Stellies will resume their campaign with a tricky clash against Golden Arrows next week Saturday afternoon at the Tuks Stadium (1:30pm). ??BREAKING??@StellenboschFC have confirmed the long-term deal with Jayden Adams who becomes their first Academy graduate to sign a professional contract with the club. #Asidlali pic.twitter.com/nERB6ERs2t  